                <abstract>William Brown (birth name unknown) was a Black woman who joined the Royal Navy under a man's name in the early nineteenth century. It is undisputed that she was a sailor of HMS Queen Charlotte, but historians have reached varying conclusions about her service record.</abstract>
                <citation>Wikipedia. "William Brown (sailor)" Accessed February 20, 2020. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Brown_(sailor)</citation>
